# LogNomaly

AI-Powered Log Anomaly Detection with Explainable AI

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10-blue)
![Machine Learning](https://img.shields.io/badge/Machine%20Learning-ScikitLearn-orange)
![ASP.NET](https://img.shields.io/badge/Backend-ASP.NET%20Core-purple)
![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-green)

LogNomaly is an explainable AI system for detecting anomalies in large-scale system logs.
It combines machine learning models, rule-based reasoning, and a web dashboard to help analysts detect and understand abnormal system behavior.

---

## System Architecture

![architecture](docs/architecture.png)

LogNomaly follows a hybrid anomaly detection pipeline:

Raw Logs → Log Parsing → Feature Extraction → Hybrid Detection → Explainable AI → Web Dashboard

The machine learning pipeline is implemented in Python while the user interface is built using ASP.NET Core MVC.

---

## Features

• Hybrid anomaly detection (Isolation Forest + Random Forest + Rule Engine)
• Explainable AI for interpretable predictions
• Automated log feature extraction pipeline
• Web dashboard for interactive log analysis
• Scalable architecture for large log datasets

