## Project Structure

```
LogNomaly
│
├── app/                # Python anomaly detection API
├── models/             # ML models and rule engine
├── utils/              # log parsing and feature extraction
├── training/           # model training scripts
├── tests/              # unit tests
├── LogNomaly.Web/      # ASP.NET web interface
└── docs/               # architecture diagrams
```

---

## Dataset

LogNomaly was evaluated using the **Blue Gene/L (BGL) log dataset**, a widely used benchmark for log anomaly detection.

Dataset statistics

• 4.7M log entries
• 348K anomalies (~7.3%)
• ~7 months of system activity

Download dataset:

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/omduggineni/loghub-bgl-log-data

Place the dataset in:

```
data/BGL.log
```

---

## Installation

Clone repository

```
git clone https://github.com/dogaece-koca/LogNomaly.git
cd LogNomaly
```

Install dependencies

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

---

## Run the AI API

```
python app/app.py
```

---

## Run the Web Dashboard

```
cd LogNomaly.Web
dotnet run
```

Open:

```
http://localhost:5000
```

